SIMPLE: preservative
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preservative
<hw>Pre*serv"a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧servatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the power or quality
of preserving; tending to preserve, or to keep from injury, decay,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preservative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Preservative
<hw>Pre*serv"a*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which preserves, or
has the power of preserving; a presevative agent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To wear tablets as <qex>preservatives</qex> against the
plague.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preservatory</ent>⟦br⟧
